oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Photograph of Brigadier General Alfred Eugene Jackson, CSA
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Photograph of Brig. Gen. Alfred Eugene Jackson, the only Confederate general from Washington County, Tenn. As military commander of Greeneville, Tenn., he saved Andrew Johnson's home. In 1863, he fought at the Battle of Limestone Station, Tenn. This photograph was included in a family album.
